import { Button as MuiButton, Grid } from '@mui/material'
import { makeStyles, withStyles } from '@material-ui/core'
import User from 'assets/user.svg'
import Help from 'assets/help.svg'
import Notification from 'assets/notification.svg'

import Icon from '../../Atoms/Icon/Icon'
import TypographyComponent from '../../Atoms/Typography/TypographyComponent'
import Dossier from 'assets/dossier-header.svg'
import Avatar from '../../Atoms/Avatar/Avatar'
import { cssClass } from '../../../Constants/constants'

export type headerProps = {}

export const Header = (props: headerProps) => {
  
  const cssClasses = cssClass();


  return (
    <Grid
      container
      direction="row"
      spacing={1}
      style={{
        border: '2px solid #D4D2D9',
        width:'1336px',
        height:'55px',        
marginTop:'-16px',
marginLeft:'-16px'

      }}
    >
      <Grid item>
        <Icon imageSrc={Dossier} classname={cssClasses.dossierIcon}></Icon>
      </Grid>
      <Grid item md={10} sm={4} style={{}}>
        <TypographyComponent
          variant="body1"
          text="DOSSIER"
          color="#4C2CD9"
          classname={cssClasses.text}
        ></TypographyComponent>
      </Grid>
      <Grid item >
        <Icon imageSrc={Help} classname={cssClasses.icon}></Icon>
      </Grid>
      <Grid item >
        <Icon imageSrc={Notification} classname={cssClasses.icon}></Icon>
      </Grid>
      <Grid item >
        <Avatar variant={'circular'} src={User}></Avatar>
      </Grid>
    </Grid>


  )
}
